Yes, this looks a bit funny to me too. But it does work!
I assume docker is using round-robin on both IP addresses of instances when resolving DNS entry for 'cps-and-ncmp' (in which case nginx simply acts as a proxy/gateway, not a load balancer).

So I suppose it could either be one entry:

    server cps-and-ncmp:8080;

or two:

    server docker-compose_cps-and-ncmp_1:8080;
    server docker-compose_cps-and-ncmp_2:8080;

Not sure of any pros/cons though

